      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRREVERENT (5) peaks off three narrow defeats, including firs- up as favourite at Sandown-Hillside. Comes back 200m and Nolen is reunited. In a top yard and is well placed to go one better. DONE LEAVY (2) resumes and is also in good hands. Was spelled off a 0.9L defeat over 1203m at Kyneton, and that stacks right up. Has been sharp at the jumpouts and will be naturally improved. FULLY FUNDED (4) just missed at Kyneton on debut and then raced a short-priced favourite at Kilmore and was found to have an issue post-race. Is back after 18 days and presented on song will be in the finish. The speedy BEAU STRADA (1) was a run short first-up. Missed a nose at Traralgon at his only second-up outing, and Egan replaces the 3kg apprentice. Has the rails gate and can control the race. She's sure to give a sight.",
